1.Use .map() to create a new array that contains the first character of each string in the animals array. Save the new array to a const variable named secretMessage.
Checkpoint 2 Passed

2.Use .map() to divide all the numbers in bigNumbers by 100. Save the returned values to a variable declared with const called smallNumbers.
solution;

const animals = ['Hen', 'elephant', 'llama', 'leopard', 'ostrich', 'Whale', 'octopus', 'rabbit', 'lion', 'dog'];

// Create the secretMessage array below
const secretMessage= animals.map(char=>{
  return char[0] ;
})

console.log(secretMessage.join(''));

const bigNumbers = [100, 200, 300, 400, 500];

// Create the smallNumbers array below

const smallNumbers=bigNumbers.map(num=>{
  return num/100;
})
