.reduce()  -> this method reduce the array into single element
1.

Let’s practice calling .reduce() and using console.log() to check the values as .reduce() iterates through the array.

In main.js, there is an array of numbers, newNumbers.

To start, declare a new variable named newSum using the const keyword. Assign to newSum the value of calling .reduce() on newNumbers. You don’t need to provide any arguments to .reduce() yet.

You’ll see a TypeError: undefined is not a function in the console after this step — we’ll fix this by adding a callback function in the next step!
Checkpoint 2 Passed

2.

Provide .reduce with an argument of a callback function. The callback function should have two parameters, accumulator and currentValue, in that order. Use either a function expression or an arrow function.
Checkpoint 3 Passed

3.

To check the value being used as we iterate through the array, add 2 logging statements to the body of the callback function:

console.log('The value of accumulator: ', accumulator);
console.log('The value of currentValue: ', currentValue);

Copy to Clipboard

Then, add a return statement that adds accumulator to currentValue.
Checkpoint 4 Passed

4.

Log the value of newSum to the console to see the return value of calling .reduce() on newNumbers.
Checkpoint 5 Passed

5.

While we have this code set up, let’s also check what happens if you add a second argument to .reduce(). The second argument acts as an initial value for the accumulator.

Add a second argument of 10 to .reduce().

solution;
const newNumbers = [1, 3, 5, 7];

const newSum=newNumbers.reduce((accumulator,currentValue)=>{
      console.log('The value of accumulator: ', accumulator);
    console.log('The value of currentValue: ', currentValue);
    return accumulator+currentValue;
},10)
console.log(newSum)
ouput;
The value of accumulator:  10
The value of currentValue:  1
The value of accumulator:  11
The value of currentValue:  3
The value of accumulator:  14
The value of currentValue:  5
The value of accumulator:  19
The value of currentValue:  7
26
